Modernization Plan at least 90 days in advance of one year after publication of the final rule to allow time for this
process. 

 

 1751.105 
 

Amending a Modernization Plan. 

 

(a) REA understands that changes in standards, technology, regulation, and the economy could indicate that an REA-approved
Modernization Plan should be amended. 

 (b) The Plan Developer of the Modernization Plan may amend the Modernization Plan if REA finds the proposed changes
continue to conform to the provisions of this subpart. 

 (c) The procedure for requesting approval of an amended Modernization Plan is identical to the procedure for a proposed
