 (1) The Modernization Plan must provide for the elimination of party line service. 

 (2) The Modernization Plan must provide for the availability of telecommunications services for improved business,
educational, and medical services. 

 (3) The Modernization Plan must encourage and improve computer networks and information highways for subscribers
in rural areas. 

 (4) The Modernization Plan must provide for: 

 (i) Subscribers in rural areas to be able to receive through telephone lines: 

 (A) Conference calling; 

 (B) Video images; and 

 (C) Data at a rate of at least 1,000,000 bits of information per second; and 




