<SUMMARY>
SUMMARY:

 EPA today proposes to designate an Ocean Dredged Material Disposal Site (ODMDS) in the Atlantic Ocean offshore Miami,
Florida, as an EPA-approved ocean dumping site for the disposal of suitable dredged material. This proposed action
is necessary to provide an acceptable ocean disposal site for consideration as an option for dredged material disposal
projects in the greater Miami, Florida vicinity. This proposed site designation is for an indefinite period of time,
but the site is subject to continuing monitoring to insure that unacceptable adverse environmental impacts do not
occur. 


